HEADWORD: Scraffle
<hw>Scraf"fle</hw> <pr>(skr⟦acr⟧f"f'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Scramble</er>: cf. OD. <ets>schraeffelen</ets> to scrape.]</ety>
<def>To scramble or struggle; to wrangle; also, to be industrious.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
